# Neural Network from Scratch

A light neural network and backpropagation framework from scratch using NumPY.
The purpose of this project is to test my understanding of the topics.

The repo remains unfinished and the readme is yet to be polished.

## California Housing Dataset

We have achieved a respectable mse loss of 0.2686 with the following hyperparameters:

<table>
    <tr>
        <td>batch size</td>
        <td>16</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>epochs</td>
        <td>200</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>base lr</td>
        <td>0.003</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>decay rate</td>
        <td>0.9999</td>
    </tr>
</table>


To run the example, make sure you are in the root directory and run the following command.

```bash
python -m examples.california_housing
```

